    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically robust example of the marque\u2019s celebrated high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six. The powertrain features individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been recently serviced for optimal phase timing. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable differential lock. To ensure structural integrity, the rear subframe has been reinforced\u2014a critical upgrade for this chassis. The suspension retains its factory-tuned kinematics with refreshed bushings and dampers, providing the tactile steering feedback and balanced weight distribution enthusiasts demand. While the paint and interior show minor signs of use consistent with a well-loved driver\u2019s car, the mechanical vitals are excellent, including a recent valve clearance adjustment and a cooling system overhaul.",
